===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|closen||to close, enclose}}, partly continuing (in altered form) earlier {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|clusen}} {{gloss|"to close"; from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|clȳsan||to close, shut}}; compare {{m|en|beclose}}, {{m|en|foreclose}}, etc.}}; and partly derived from the {{etyl|enm|en}} adjective {{m|enm|clos||close, shut up, confined, secret}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|clos||close, confined|pos=adjective}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|clausus||shut up|pos=past participle}}, from {{m|la|claudere||to bar, block, close, enclose, bring an end to, confine}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*klāw-||key, hook, nail}}, related to {{cog|la|clāvis||key, deadbolt, bar}}, {{m|la|clāvus||nail, peg}}, {{m|la|claustrum||bar, bolt, barrier}}, {{m|la|claustra||dam, wall, barricade, stronghold}}. Cognate with {{cog|grc|κλείς||bar, bolt, key}}, {{cog|de|schließen||to close, conclude, lock}}, {{cog|nl|sluiten||to close, conclude, lock}}. Replaced {{cog|ang|lūcan||to close, lock, enclose}}.

